Package gw.api.database.preload

Class ArrayLoader<P extends KeyableBean,C extends KeyableBean>

java.lang.Object
gw.api.database.preload.ArrayLoader<P,C>
Type Parameters:
P - Parent type
C - Child type
All Implemented Interfaces:
Iterable<C>
public final class ArrayLoader<P extends KeyableBean,C extends KeyableBean> extends Object implements Iterable<C>
Loads the children of the specified IArrayPropertyInfo for each provided parent. Loading is complete when an iteration is complete.

If ArrayMembershipCacheStrategy.Cache is used, array membership will be cached at the bundle level instead of the Global Cache level. The bundle's array membership cache is updated with each complete iteration of ArrayLoader and the cache is cleared when the bundle is committed.

Indirectly holds a reference to the bundle.

This iterable uses IQueryResult and therefore calling iterator() twice will issue another query.

Results of ArrayLoader should only be used for preloading and not for business logic as getters can be overloaded.

This class is not thread-safe.

Default Query CacheControl is LOAD_USING_AND_UPDATE_GLOBAL_CACHE. Default ArrayMembershipCacheStrategy is Cache except for ReadOnlyBundle, it is DoNotCache.
